This would be a fine standard.  However, it doesn't have to be part of the
_Unicode_ standard, and I don't think it belongs as a normative part of
Unicode.  As minimal as it may be, it still falls into the domain of file
formats and "higher-level protocol".

It's a tribute to the success of Unicode that people want to piggyback on
it's success to solve closely related problems. 

