You've got to be kidding!  Of the thousands of web sites I have browsed, I can
count the number I find legible on one hand.  It is so bad now that I don't
even bother reading web pages; I just look for URL's.

And don't blame the systems and mail handlers for not dealing with markup
because most of them do so in one way or another.  The point is that those of
us working in plain text are doing so by choice, not necessity.  And why do we
choose plain text?  In my case, I find that text with markup noticeably slows
my reading speed and comprehension.  In short, if the text isn't "designed"
well enough, I can't read it and usually just delete it.
