Hummed to Ein feste Burg, these lines require the addition of
phantom syllables for the extra notes:

     All such no(uh)tions be(ee) conceit,
     but Plai(ai)n Text is for(or)-e-ver..

Whereas, Frank's text scans as a perfect iambic pentameter blank verse
couplet:

     But all such notions are ephemeral,
      -   '   -    '  -    '  -  ' - '
     And plain text is forever -- Frank da Cruz.
      -   '     -   '   - ' -       '    -   '

A suitable contribution to "The Unic Ode".

--Ken

